<h2><a name="section1">FAQ/Help</a></h2>

<h3>What is smartn.me?</h3>
<p>smartn.me is an alternative way to fund your education. This site was created to combat the rising debt from student loans and to shine a light on the many different ways that people are educating themselves around the world.</p>

<h3>How exactly does smartn.me work?</h3>
<p>smartn.me is a crowdfunding platform to aide students in raising money to fund their studies. All campaigns must have an educational purpose and a specified time period (between 1 and 90 days). After a campaign is approved, the student has to engage their community & networks to raise the money that has been requested. When a deadline is reached there will be one of two outcomes, which we call the “all-or-nothing” approach:
</br>1. The Successful campaign: if the goal is reached or exceeded, the campaign owner gets all of the money raised.
</br>2. The Unsuccessful campaign: if the goal isn't reached, we will return all contributions to the supporters of that campaign and the student gets nothing.</p>

<h3>And why all-or-nothing?</h3>
<p>Simply put: It's less risky</i>. Donors need to be sure that you'll use the money accordingly, and we assume that the minimum amount you’ve requested is the amount necessary to carry out your goal. If you don’t reach this monetary target, then it would be very difficult to fund the goal you're pursuing.</li>
The "All or Nothing" approach definitely gives extra motivation to be proactive in your attempt at raising money</i>. Your task is to get as many people involved as possible. When people see that you are enthusiastic and actively working to fund your education, they will be more inclined to help.</p>

<h3>What type of campaigns can be found on smartn.me?</h3>
<p>smartn.me is dedicated to educational campaigns only, however this doesn’t mean that it’s only for college students. At smartn.me we disagree with the notion that an education has to come from a university. We challenge people all over the world to think outside of the box and take a more proactive approach to learning and bettering themselves. With that being said here are just a few examples of what this encompasses: college, art school, exam fees &amp; test preparation, tuition, books, specialized training courses, studying abroad, ETC. If you have any questions about the types of campaigns that will be accepted, just send us an email and we’d be happy to discuss it with you. Or submit your campaign and we’ll contact you within two days to let you know if it’s approved or not. 
